      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T19:10:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Will do it a follow up instead. My understanding from the old comments \"call the non-virtual version\" was that it was intended to just go to the base SkCanvas\u0027s drawing code for the simpler shape (rect or oval). As it stands, it goes to the public non-virtual, which then calls the onDraw virtual. This means that a naive recording canvas will record a drawRRect and a drawRect if the SkRRect.isRect() returns true.\n\nWhat we really want is to just go straight to SkCanvas::onDrawX and skip any further touching by subclasses, since it\u0027s purely a drawing optimization in onDrawRRect to simplify the representation.",
      "parentUuid": "bc54e074_bbdef434",
