      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T15:53:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Let\u0027s stick to the old style here?  I find it easier to follow the three cases with early returns separately.  Written this way it makes it look like the first two are somehow more tightly related than just neither draws, where really it\u0027s the second and third cases that are closer parallels.\n\nOr is there a way we can not check path.isFinite() and instead leave that for quick_reject() and pathBounds?\n\n(I do like the third case flattened out into inverse \u0026\u0026 width\u003d0 \u0026\u0026 height\u003d0 like this though.)",
      "range": {
