        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T19:10:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, see for instance line 2499 in the old diff. The code basically did extra hoops while \u0027paint\u0027 was null, but always ended up setting \u0027paint\u0027 back to a default SkPaint before calling into SkDevice.\n\nI have another CL here: https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/341056 that cleans this up more to just SkTCopyOnWrite for the draw calls that need to canonize the input paint and handle null paints (side note, I would like null paint to just go away...)",
      "parentUuid": "0117ecca_3de6dfb8",
      "revId": "70b0c520af88e5b162a5f23d73f19e7b4db8f513",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
